TITLE: Rapper Tory Lanez is found guilty on all charges in the shooting of Megan Thee Stallion
SUMMARY: Megan Thee Stallion accused Lanez of shooting her in the foot during an argument after the pair left a party at Kylie Jenner’s home in July 2020

TITLE: Target issues recall for more than 200,000 weighted blankets after 2 children die
SUMMARY: The girls, ages 4 and 6, died in Camp Lejeune, North Carolina, after they were trapped in the blankets in April, federal officials said

TITLE: Idaho professor sues TikToker over allegations in the killing of 4 university students
SUMMARY: The University of Idaho history professor accuses the TikToker of defamation in a federal lawsuit, saying videos with the allegations have been viewed millions of times

TITLE: Multiple people dead and more than 1M in the dark as winter storm brings bitter cold to much of the U.S.
SUMMARY: As conditions worsen, thousands of flights have been canceled or delayed, upending holiday travel plans for many

TITLE: Target issues recall for more than 200,000 weighted blankets after 2 children die
SUMMARY: A young child can become entrapped by unzipping and entering the blanket, posing a risk of death by asphyxiation, the company says

TITLE: Kari Lake loses suit over her defeat in Arizona governor’s race
SUMMARY: A judge found Saturday that the court did not find convincing evidence of the widespread misconduct that Lake alleged had affected the result of the 2022 general election

TITLE: 5 arrested in fatal shooting of 19-year-old at Nordstrom in Mall of America, police say
SUMMARY: The victim, whose identity has not been released, was shot during a fight Friday night, the Bloomington, Minn., police chief said. No other injuries were reported

TITLE: Live updates: Deadly winter storm brings blizzards and dangerous wind chills to much of the U.S.
SUMMARY: Travel will be "extremely dangerous" and "at times impossible" where whiteout conditions occur, the National Weather Service said

TITLE: First openly transgender woman set to be executed in the U.S. asks for mercy
SUMMARY: Lawyers for Amber McLaughlin, now 49, on Monday asked Missouri Gov. Mike Parson to spare her. McLaughlin was convicted of killing 45-year-old Beverly Guenther in 2003

TITLE: Father of Texas girl allegedly killed by FedEx driver files lawsuit
SUMMARY: The suit accuses the driver, Tanner Lynn Horner, FedEx, and its subcontractor Big Topspin of negligence
